## What is a Function?

A function is a block of code that performs a specific task.

It can be called whenever needed.

Functions are commonly used in procedural programming languages like C.

Example (C Language)

int add(int a, int b){
    return a + b;
}

---

## What is a Method?

A method is a function that belongs to a class.

In Java, all functions are written inside classes, so they are called methods.

Example

public class Test {

    int add(int a, int b){
        return a + b;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args){

        Test t = new Test();

        int result = t.add(10,20);

        System.out.println(result);
    }

}

Output

30

---

## Difference Between Function and Method

Function

- Independent block of code
- Used in procedural programming
- Can exist outside a class

Method

- Defined inside a class
- Used in object-oriented programming
- Called using an object or class
